      "id": 80799,
      "title": "Overview",
      "content": "# Waste Sorting Detection Challenge\n\n## About\nDetect and classify waste objects from real conveyor belt images captured. Build the best object detection model across 19 waste categories.\n\n## Dataset\n- Train: 5,238 images with YOLO format labels\n- Test: 1,312 images\n\n\n## Classes (19 total)\n| ID | Class | ID | Class |\n|----|-------|----|-------|\n| 0 | pet-bottle-clear | 10 | sachet |\n| 1 | pet-bottle-green | 11 | tetrapack |\n| 2 | ldpe-clear | 12 | cardboard-brown |\n| 3 | ldpe-hm | 13 | paper-box |\n| 4 | ldpe-black | 14 | coconut-shell |\n| 5 | hdpe-bottle | 15 | footwear |\n| 6 | metal-can | 16 | idpe-colored |\n| 7 | milk-packet | 17 | hard-plastic |\n| 8 | pp-bag | 18 | other |\n| 9 | mlp-packet | | |\n\n## How to Participate\n1. Access the workstation via SSH (credentials shared separately)\n2. Train your model on the provided dataset\n3. Generate predictions.json on the workstation\n4. Submit predictions.json here on Codabench\n\n## Submission Format\nSubmit a single predictions.json file in COCO detection format:\n\n[\n  {\n    \"image_id\": 0,\n    \"category_id\": 3,\n    \"bbox\": [x_min, y_min, width, height],\n    \"score\": 0.91\n  },\n  ...\n]\n\n- image_id: 0-based index (images sorted alphabetically)\n- category_id: integer 0-18\n- bbox: absolute pixel coordinates [x_min, y_min, width, height]\n- score: confidence between 0 and 1\n\n## Metrics\n- Primary rank: mAP50\n- Tiebreaker: mAP50-95\n- Also shown: Precision, Recall, F1, per-class AP for all 19 classes\n\n## Rules\n- Max 3 official submissions per day\n- Any framework allowed (YOLO, RT-DETR, Detectron2...)\n- Pretrained backbones allowed (COCO pretrain OK)\n- Do not share credentials or workstation access\n- Dataset must not be copied or downloaded",
      "index": 0
    }
  ],
